==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overpower
<hw>O`ver*pow"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overpowered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overpowering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To excel or exceed
in power; to cause to yield by superior power; to vanquish; to subdue;
<as>as, the light <ex>overpowers</ex> the eyes</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧And
<xex>overpower'd</xex> that gallant few.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To overbear; overcome; vanquish; defeat; crush;
overwhelm; overthrow; rout; conquer; subdue.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overpower</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overpower
<hw>O"ver*pow`er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dominating power.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overpowered</ent>⟦br⟧
